caption:
☀️ Heard the term photostability in sunscreens? Let’s decode it.
Photostability = your sunscreen’s ability to stay effective even after sun exposure.
If a formula breaks down under UV rays, it stops protecting your skin!
That’s why it matters.

✨ The good news? Lakmē sunscreens use photostable UV filters.
So your protection doesn’t quit when the sun comes out.
